"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource"},{"text":"’s polygons collectively using an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource"},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer"},{"text":" object. To access a polygon’s attributes, use an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Alternatively, you can add a polygon overlay directly to a map view using the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addOverlay:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" method. Configure","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a polygon overlay’s appearance using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:strokeColorForShapeAnnotation:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:fillColorForPolygonAnnotation:","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The vertices are automatically connected in the order in which you provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"them. You should close the polygon by specifying the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as the first and last vertices; otherwise, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polygon’s fill may not cover the area you expect it to. To avoid filling the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"space within the shape, give the polygon a transparent fill or use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A polygon may have one or more interior polygons, or holes, that you specify as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"reference"},{"text":" objects with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"+polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method. For example, if a polygon represents a lake, it could exclude an island","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"within the lake using an interior polygon. Interior polygons may not themselves","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"have interior polygons. To represent a shape that includes a polygon within a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"hole or, more generally, to group multiple polygons together in one shape, use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","type":"reference"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","type":"reference"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To make the polygon straddle the antimeridian, specify some longitudes less"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"than −180 degrees or greater than 180 degrees."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Related-examples","type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Related examples"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"TODO: Add a polygon annotation, learn how to initialize an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" object from an array of coordinates.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint"],"kind":"relationships"},{"title":"Inherited By","type":"inheritedBy","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature"],"kind":"relationships"},{"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"],"kind":"relationships"}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygon/polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:","type":"topic","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon\/polygonwithcoordinates:count:interiorpolygons:","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates and returns an "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object from the specified set of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"coordinates and interior polygons."}],"title":"polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:","fragments":[{"kind":"text","text":"+ "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}],"title":"MLNOverlay","role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNShape":{"type":"topic","title":"MLNShape","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnshape","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","fragments":[{"text":"MLNShape","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is an abstract class that represents a shape or annotation. Shapes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"constitute the content of a map — not only the overlays atop the map, but also","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the content that forms the base map.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNEmptyFeature":{"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNEmptyFeature"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnemptyfeature","kind":"symbol","title":"MLNEmptyFeature","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNEmptyFeature"},{"type":"text","text":" object associates an empty shape with an optional"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identifier and attributes."}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNEmptyFeature"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPointCollectionFeature":{"title":"MLNPointCollectionFeature","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollectionFeature"},{"text":" object associates a point collection with an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"optional identifier and attributes.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"MLNPointCollectionFeature","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpointcollectionfeature","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollectionFeature","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNSymbolStyleLayer":{"title":"MLNSymbolStyleLayer","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer"},{"type":"text","text":" is a style layer that renders icon and text labels"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at points or along lines on the map."}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNSymbolStyleLayer","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnsymbolstylelayer"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygonFeature":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygonfeature","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPolygonFeature","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MLNPolygonFeature","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature"},{"type":"text","text":" object associates a polygon shape with an optional"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identifier and attributes."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolygon":{"title":"MLNMultiPolygon","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMultiPolygon"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polygons that do not overlap. For example, you could use a multipolygon shape"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to represent the body of land that consists of an island surrounded by an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"atoll: the inner island would be one "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object, while the surrounding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"atoll would be another. You could also use a multipolygon shape to represent a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group of disconnected but related buildings."}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolygon"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolyline":{"kind":"symbol","title":"MLNMultiPolyline","fragments":[{"kind":"i